# Expected SHA-256 of sim-tme-3d's default 24-condition matrix summary.json.
#
# This pins the byte-identity invariant that the #239 multi-dose PK work
# leans on: when every condition uses DoseSchedule::Constant (the entire
# default matrix), summary.json must be byte-for-byte identical to its
# pre-#239 output. The fast `constant_path_golden_kill_counts` unit test
# guards per-PR drift at a small 20^3 x 80 config; this file guards the
# FULL 60^3 x 180 production output via the (off-PR) sim-tme-3d-regression
# workflow.
#
# TOOLCHAIN-SPECIFIC: this hash is only stable on the pinned channel in
# simulations/rust-toolchain.toml (currently 1.96.0). powf / Ziggurat are
# not bit-identical across libm versions. Confirmed identical on 1.92.0
# and 1.96.0, so it is stable in practice for the pinned channel.
#
# Regenerate ONLY when an INTENTIONAL output change lands (and say why in
# the PR):
#   cd simulations
#   rustup run 1.96.0 cargo run --release -p sim-tme-3d
#   sha256sum output/tme-3d/summary.json   # paste the hash below
#
# Verify (what CI does), from the simulations/ directory:
#   sha256sum -c sim-tme-3d/expected_summary.sha256
#
# (Lines beginning with '#' are ignored by `sha256sum -c`.)
#
# RE-BASELINED in #578 (INTENTIONAL — this is the maintainer-approved
# re-baseline the #253 gate is designed to require for a deliberate output
# change). The per-cell RNG seed changed from the #539 additive-stride scheme
# (`cond_seed + offset + idx + step*STRIDE`, which aliased above ~1e6 cells)
# to the position+step-independent `cell_seed` SplitMix64 hash mix, removing
# the large-grid collision regime. This reshuffles every per-cell RNG draw, so
# the summary.json bytes change BY DESIGN. At the dim-60 production matrix the
# old scheme was ALREADY collision-free, so this is a pure RNG-stream reshuffle,
# NOT a behavioral change: the headline DIRECTIONS are unchanged (verified
# old-vs-new — overall_kill_rate moves <0.1% on the headline uniform conditions
# (Control 0.000%, RSL3 0.069%, SDT 0.005%); the largest overall_kill_rate shift
# is 1.46% on a low-magnitude RSL3-gradient cell. Near-zero fields (e.g.
# transition_kill_rate, ~0.0006) move more in RELATIVE terms but only by a
# handful of cells in absolute count. Hypoxia asymmetry SDT>>RSL3>Control and
# every gradient/immune ordering preserved). Prior hash: 1cf8866312c100bfb453718dfd68e0b492d2e199485e75e8f622657cd390ff71.
# The hash below was generated on the pinned 1.96.0 toolchain; the prior baseline
# was byte-identical on macOS/aarch64 and the CI ubuntu/x86_64 regression, and
# the sim-tme-3d-regression run dispatched on this PR confirms the new value.
973d9443bd05851721d53d9a15e53dc828517bba4bf307eb1c4f0b1f60d27289  output/tme-3d/summary.json
